    <h2>My job</h2>
       
    <div>   
        <p>I work at the University of Victoria <a href="https://hcmc.uvic.ca/">Humanities Computing and Media Centre</a>
        as a Programmer/Analyst. I work primarily on digital editions of literary and historical texts, indigenous language
        dictionaries, and other humanities websites and publications, mostly using <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/xml/">XML</a> 
            technologies (<a href="https://www.tei-c,org/">TEI</a> XML, <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/xslt-30/">XSLT</a>, 
            <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/xquery-30/">XQuery</a>,
            <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/XHTML#XHTML5">XHTML5</a>, 
            <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/xsl/">XSL:FO</a>) as well as 
            <a href="https://www.latex-project.org/">LaTeX</a>, JavaScript, and CSS. I am particularly focused on creating sustainable, resilient
            websites which require no maintenance because they are 
            <a href="https://endings.uvic.ca/compliance.html">Endings-compliant</a>. Iʼve worked as a programmer and 
        collaborator on many projects, including:</p>
        
        <ul>
